[thinking] **Evaluating servlet versions**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about how the generated scaffold may need to create test doubles that implement interfaces. It seems that Servlet 2.3’s HttpServletRequest has fewer methods than 2.4, which might actually make it easier to create stubs implementing the interface since there are fewer methods to handle with 2.3. This could lead to a simpler testing process, and that’s definitely a good thing!
[thinking] 
